<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">When I have a larrikan's mask (which is rather rare now) I do tend to use it slowly, it's not b/c I never need or would like invis though, it's b/c I have to gauge when I need those 10 charges the *most*.

In general I run nearly everywhere w/o invis, DA and DB are pretty good for getting past big things and I have pretty high ac/hp so I can take a few hits.  But there are certainly times where it's gotten me killed (that lovely white dragon in WL procced 1250 dmg on me twice in a row then whacked me for 750 to finish me off while I was running through WL unbuffed one night)

As a raiding cleric in the high end game I normally have to run through WW at *least* once a night, sometimes naked (grats bugged corpse).  The invis spell would be wonderful for this.

At the very least if they dont want to give us invis they need to make the potions stackable or charged , and they need to be available in EVERY city.  As it stands now being on giant faction I can't buy invis pots at all in velious.

